rsity of Georgia."]}]},{"name":"Ann","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Anne .  In the U.S. <i>Ann</i> is the more frequent spelling."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":15,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1355924,"age":107,"year":"1547","julianDay":2286090,"description":"Henry VIII dies, succeeded by the boy king Edward VI. England and Ireland were ruled by the senior nobility of England.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705201,"age":109,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Ann Claye was born in 1440, in Ireland. She had at least 1 son with John Thomas Claye. She lived in Derbyshire, England in 1501. She died in 1558, in Chesterfield, Derbyshire, England, at the age of 118."},"et":{"1440–1558":"1440–1558","1440–1532":"1440–1532","1502–1532":"1502–1532","1558":"1558","1547":"1547","1502":"1502","1532":"1532","1455":"1455"